Commentary: back of a length on middle, and he pulls along the ground to fine leg. Drinks - fourth umpire S Ravi brings out bananas for the umpires
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Miller, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length, outside off stump. Pulled along the ground to deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Miller, 1 run

Commentary: length ball, on middle, and worked away to the leg side
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to van der Dussen, no run

Commentary: length ball on middle, and angling into his body. Flicked off his hips to the leg side
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to van der Dussen, 1 leg bye

Commentary: back of a length, wide outside off, and cut behind square to deep point
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Miller, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length, on off, and the short ball is left alone by Rassie
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to van der Dussen, no run

Commentary: full, on leg stump, and going down leg. Rassie isn't happy that wasn't called a wide, but reckon it came off his boot
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to van der Dussen, no run

Commentary: back of a length, on middle, and pulled. Finds midwicket
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Miller, no run

Commentary: back of a length, on middle, and Miller pulls out of his hook. Umpire says 'first bouncer'
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Miller, no run

Commentary: back of a length, slower ball from Wahab. Wide outside off, and cut over the infield. Protection at deep point though
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Miller, 1 run

Commentary: dropped by the captain! Full, on middle, and he goes for an expansive leg-side slog. Leading edge takes it past the keeper's right, and he can't hold on either
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to van der Dussen, 1 run

Commentary: dropped again! Amir once more. Back of a length outside off, and he tries to guide a cute ramp-shot near third man. Amir does all the effort, but then drops the catch as he tries to slide across the ground. Apologises to Wahab
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Miller, 1 run

Commentary: full, on middle, and lofted over the bowler. Not timed well enough, but enough to clear mid-on. Poor Wahab!
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to van der Dussen, 2 runs

Commentary: overpitched, outside off, and he creams a drive through the covers! In the slot, and punished
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Miller, FOUR runs

Commentary: back of a length, outside off, and he shapes to pull. Ball stays low and goes through him to Sarfaraz
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Miller, no run
Shaheen Shah Afridi to Miller, 1 run

Commentary: that's outta here! Full from around the wicket, and he tees off. Proper golfswing and that's gone over cow corner. Boom!
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to van der Dussen, SIX runs

Commentary: yorker on off stump. Well covered from Shaheen. Leading edge takes it to short third man instead, but they manage to take the single
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to van der Dussen, 1 run

Commentary: full outside off, and he swings to the leg side. Slices the shot, but just past Amir at midwicket
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Miller, 2 runs

Commentary: back of a length, on middle, and it hits van der Dussen near the helmet grille. Shrugs it off and walks across for one
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to van der Dussen, 1 run

Commentary: full, on off, and punched down the ground. Wahab can't stop it, and that means they can scamper across for one
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Miller, 1 run

Commentary: full, outside leg stump, and he tries to whip it behind square. Misses though
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to van der Dussen, 1 wide

Commentary: slower ball, length on leg stump and van der Dussen is through his pull too early. Hits him near the gut, and rolls away to the off side. Well deceived!
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to van der Dussen, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length outside off, and skidding through. Miller tried to cut but it was too close to his body
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Miller, no run

Commentary: nearly clipped off stump! And offcutter angling in, and Miller tees up for the slog. Misses, and just goes over his stumps. Wry smile from the bowler
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Miller, no run

Commentary: length ball, on off stump, and Miller shapes to pull again. Misses once more
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Miller, no run

Commentary: length ball outside off, and the legbreak forces him to miss the cut
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to van der Dussen, no run

Commentary: another length ball outside off, but this time it turns further away. Well taken by Sarfaraz but that's a wide for sure
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to van der Dussen, 1 wide

Commentary: tucked off his hips to deep midwicket, but they settle for only one. Is Miller's groin bothering him?
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to van der Dussen, 1 run

Commentary: yorker, on leg stump, and he punches this just over Shadab! Protection at long off though
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Miller, 1 run

Commentary: the professor gets A+! Full, on off, and Rassie tries to slog towards the leg side. But the slice goes in the air for ages, and Hafeez - from cover point - keeps his eyes on the ball and dives forward to complete a very difficult chance
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to van der Dussen, OUT
Dismissal_text: HE van der Dussen c Mohammad Hafeez b Shadab Khan 36 (71m 47b 1x4 1x6) SR: 76.59

Commentary: length ball, just outside off. Cut to point
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Miller, no run

Commentary: lbw appeal, and given! Miller reviews. This was full on middle, and turning across Miller. He misses the sweep, and ball hits front leg. But was it spinning too much? Replays say that it hit him in front of middle stump, but there's a thin under-edge. Miller survives!
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Miller, no run

Commentary: wide of off stump, Phehlukwayo drives through the offside to get Miller on strike
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Phehlukwayo, 1 run

Commentary: opens the face of the bat and strikes it to the same fielder. This won't do for South Africa
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Miller, 1 run

Commentary: shaping back in to Phehlukwayo, and defended back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Phehlukwayo, no run

Commentary: gets it through the covers to deep extra again
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Phehlukwayo, 1 run

Commentary: slower delivery, and it does Miller. It's probably done South Africa in the process! Rolled his fingers over it, and Miller was looking to open up the offside. The ball clips the top of middle and leg, dismantling the stumps
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Miller, OUT
Dismissal_text: DA Miller  b Shaheen Shah Afridi 31 (54m 37b 3x4 0x6) SR: 83.78

Commentary: gets off the mark with a prod through the offside. Asking rate nearly 13 now
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Morris, 1 run

Commentary: googly, driven down the ground
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Morris, 1 run

Commentary: faster ball. Phehlukwayo just about gets his bat to it
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Phehlukwayo, 1 run

Commentary: defended back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Morris, no run

Commentary: charges down the wicket but only finds long-on
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Morris, 1 run

Commentary: reverse sweep comes out and he gets it horribly wrong. Hits his boot on the full. Massive appeal but the umpire's unmoved
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Phehlukwayo, no run

Commentary: plonked down the wicket to long-on. Shadab puts in a nice dive for the cameras but the ball's well wide of him
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Phehlukwayo, 1 run

Commentary: tailed back in, and Phehlukwayo was fortunate to get an inside edge to it, even luckier to see it roll away for four
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Phehlukwayo, FOUR runs

Commentary: hits the deck hard, blocked
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Phehlukwayo, no run

Commentary: width, and cut away to deep point, where a decent bit of fielding from Imam saves a few runs
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Phehlukwayo, 1 run

Commentary: bouncer, but is wide enough to allow Morris to free his arms and guide it down to third man. Shaheen came around the wicket, presumably to tie Morris up, but didn't quite execute
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Morris, FOUR runs

Commentary: one of the shots of the day. Driven in the air, followed the line of the ball, which is deposited into the stand behind long-off. Morris still believes.
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Morris, SIX runs

Commentary: full toss that Morris failed to time. Was in the air for a precariously long time, but Babar couldn't quite get to it
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Morris, 1 run

Commentary: driven to mid-off, only a single
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Morris, 1 run

Commentary: googly, but is a bit too short. Allows Andile to make some room and slice it away to deep point
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Phehlukwayo, 1 run

Commentary: Shadab got away with that one. Dragged it down, but Morris couldn't beat the man at long-off
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Morris, 1 run

Commentary: slog swept. Shadab bowled the conventional legspinner, and ANdile was quick onto it! Right to cow corner, where it reaches the boundary after one bounce
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Phehlukwayo, FOUR runs

Commentary: flat, quick ball. Nearly caught the batsman out
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Phehlukwayo, no run

Commentary: scooped up again. Phehlukwayo is going after everything now. Only one this time, though. 8 off the over. Decent, but not nearly enough
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Phehlukwayo, 1 run

Commentary: quick from Wahab, as you might expect. Tails into him, and perhaps for the best he gets off strike quickly
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Phehlukwayo, 1 run

Commentary: does the job, as Wahab has for much of this tournament. 92mph, and while Morris might be good for a bash or two, that speed, combined with the leg stump yorker length, is just too good for him. Another nail in an already well-sealed South African coffin, you'd sense
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Morris, OUT
Dismissal_text: CH Morris  b Wahab Riaz 16 (16m 10b 1x4 1x6) SR: 160.00

Commentary: right on the money. Perfect yorker. Rabada does well to keep it out
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Rabada, no run

Commentary: driven to mid-off, and Rabada gets off strike
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Rabada, 1 run

Commentary: short ball, but it's well over the batsman's head. Called by the square leg umpire
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Phehlukwayo, 1 wide

Commentary: full toss, edged down to deep square
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Phehlukwayo, 1 run

Commentary: tailing into the ribs, fended off to mid-on by Rabada.
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Rabada, no run

Commentary: heave-ho from Phehlukwayo. Gets an inside edge down to fine leg
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Phehlukwayo, 1 run

Commentary: slower ball, Rabada taps and gets himself off strike
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Rabada, 1 run

Commentary: pulled away nicely to square leg. Imam-ul-Haq dives to his right to prevent the boundary. He's had a good day, has the left-hander
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Phehlukwayo, 2 runs

Commentary: full and wide. Wild swing and a miss
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Phehlukwayo, no run

Commentary: dragged down to the leg side, a knee high full toss. Rare bad delivery from Amir, and Phehlukwayo punishes him by finding the gap at cow corner again
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Phehlukwayo, FOUR runs

Commentary: slower bouncer, and Andile will swing at everything now. Gets the top edge and sees it trickle down to the fine leg boundary. This will hurt Pakistan's NRR, which, in the end, is all it could come down to
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Phehlukwayo, FOUR runs

Commentary: attempted yorker. Tails back in  but slightly overpitched. Rabada gets an inside edge or it would have uprooted middle stump
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Rabada, no run

Commentary: thick inside edge gets him to the other end
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Rabada, 1 run

Commentary: beaten for pace outside off stump. Phehlukwayo looked to cut, and found himself late on the shot
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Phehlukwayo, no run

Commentary: fast and into the body. Punched down the ground
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Phehlukwayo, 1 run

Commentary: this had been on the cards ever since Wahab began bowling to Rabada. Another full toss that he gets to swing back in. Full toss again, but the tail is enough to penetrate the gap between bat and pad, and take middle stump with it
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Rabada, OUT
Dismissal_text: K Rabada  b Wahab Riaz 3 (13m 7b 0x4 0x6) SR: 42.85

Commentary: too good for Ngidi, that. Wahab came around the wicket, and the reverse swing took it away from the expansive drive the number ten was looking to play
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Ngidi, no run

Commentary: full and wide, much too wide on this occasion. Right, Amir will be looking to wrap this up.
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Phehlukwayo, 1 wide

Commentary: slower ball. Phehlukwayo swings, as they say, like a rusty gate
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Phehlukwayo, no run

Commentary: squeezed behind square. That's a nice dig from Andile, who's putting together a nice, if inconsequential, innings. Shaheen dives at the boundary, but can't stop it trickling towards the rope
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Phehlukwayo, FOUR runs

Commentary: driven through the covers. Ngidi on strike. Is this Amir's chance to take the lead at the top of the wickets charts?
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Phehlukwayo, 1 run

Commentary: swing and a miss. It was another cutter, but Ngidi didn't quite look like he spotted that
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Ngidi, no run

Commentary: another slower ball, and poor Ngidi didn't have a clue about that one. Just missed the off stump
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Ngidi, no run

Commentary: chunky edge down to third man. They take the single, which means Ngidi will face Wahab next over. That could be fun ... for Wahab
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Ngidi, 1 run

Commentary: 144mph, that one. Had it been on target Ngidi would have been walking back
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Ngidi, no run

Commentary: he is now. Length ball this time which moved away, perhaps off the seam. Ngidi's bat nowhere near the line of its trajectory, and Pakistan are one wicket away
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Ngidi, OUT
Dismissal_text: L Ngidi  b Wahab Riaz 1 (9m 6b 0x4 0x6) SR: 16.66

Commentary: what was going on there? Imran Tahir blocked, and just set off like a man who had determined he would not be facing one more ball from Wahab than necessary, Direct hit would have been curtains
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Imran Tahir, 1 run

Commentary: slower ball, driven down to deep cover. Here's Wahab's chance to pick up a four-fer
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Phehlukwayo, 1 run

Commentary: gets his bat on that one, straight to mid-on. Last ball of Wahab's spell. Will it be the last ball of this contest?
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Imran Tahir, no run

Commentary: nearly. Nearly. Came back over the wicket, but Imran just about got the outside of his bat to it
Commentary_short: Wahab Riaz to Imran Tahir, no run

Commentary: spanked down the ground from Phehlukwayo. Comes back for two, and that brings up South Africa's 250
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Phehlukwayo, 2 runs

Commentary: didn't middle that at all, but the edge was thick enough to take it square of third man, and they come back for a couple
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Phehlukwayo, 2 runs

Commentary: top edge. Shaheen Afridi never quite charged at it like he might have done. Is that a run out? They've gone upstairs. No it's not. Carry on
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Phehlukwayo, 2 runs

Commentary: driven through the covers. This one was middled nicely, and a sloppy attempt on the boundary by Fakhar means South Africa get a four
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Phehlukwayo, FOUR runs

Commentary: rapped on the foot. Right, can Andile get his half-century. Needs a six ti make it happen
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Phehlukwayo, no run

Commentary: full and on the stumps. Phehlukwayo tonks it down to cow corner, but there's a fielder there this time. Pakistan have won by 49 runs, and are very much alive in this World Cup
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Phehlukwayo, 1 run
